  "text": "The above fi ndings cumulatively implied that nuclear and cytoplasmic Fe (III) (probably stored in the form of ferritin and sequestrated in lysosomes) in the PCT was reduced into chelatable Fe (II) by some reducing agents activated or generated in the kidneys during ischemia or ischemia/reperfusion; the nuclear relocation of some cytoplasmic Fe 2+ generated by reduction of Fe (III) during ischemia/reperfusion is also probable [CITATION_1] .",
